FAQ_SUBTITLE_PLACEHOLDER_TEXT: Get the purrfect answers to your cat image UI questions
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_1: How can I display cat images on my website?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_1: You can use HTML tags to display cat images on your website. Simply provide the source file path or URL to the image you want to display.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_2: What image formats work best for cat pictures?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_2: JPG and PNG formats are recommended for displaying high-quality cat images on the web. These formats strike a good balance between image quality and file size.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_3: How can I make cat images responsive?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_3: Use CSS to make your cat images responsive and adapt to different screen sizes. Setting max-width:100% and height:auto will ensure images scale properly.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_4: Can I create image galleries for my cat pics?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_4: Absolutely! You can use CSS or JavaScript to create sleek image galleries showcasing your furry feline friends. Popular libraries like Lightbox make this easy.
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_QUESTION_TEXT_5: How can I optimize cat images for fast loading?
FAQ_PLACEHOLDER_ANSWER_TEXT_5: Compress your images using tools like TinyPNG to reduce file sizes. You can also use the HTML picture element with srcset to load different sized images based on the user's screen.
